&lt;div&gt;At Mather Place, wellness is not an add‑on—it’s a way of life. As the Spa &amp;amp; Fitness Manager, you will lead a comprehensive, hospitality‑driven wellness experience that integrates fitness, aquatics, spa/salon services, and holistic signature programs into meaningful, high‑quality offerings for residents across the continuum. In this highly visible leadership role, you will design, implement, schedule, and measure individualized and group wellness programs across indoor and outdoor spaces, as well as virtual and on‑demand platforms, ensuring programs reflect diverse abilities, interests, and goals; &lt;strong&gt;this includes directly creating and teaching a variety of fitness class modalities and developing personalized and group fitness programs. You will also oversee spa and salon services by supporting and managing spa specialists and their offerings, without directly providing spa services. Y&lt;/strong&gt;ou will manage wellness amenity spaces and equipment, oversee and develop independent contractors and wellness specialists, and collaborate closely with external vendors, community partners, and internal Resident Engagement colleagues to ensure program excellence, safety, and innovation. This is a full‑time, salaried (exempt), 100% in‑person leadership role offering scheduling flexibility across days, evenings, and weekends, &lt;strong&gt;ideal for a fitness‑focused manager&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;who brings hands‑on experience leading and facilitating engaging fitness programs&lt;/strong&gt;, and who thrives on building relationships, inspiring others, and delivering exceptional wellness experiences.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures that Mather brand standards for resident engagement and wellness are the drivers behind strategic planning of fitness center, spa services, and signature wellness initiatives, supporting autonomy, achievement, and affiliation within individuals and the community system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develops schedule and manages delivery of fitness and holistic wellness programs within Get Fit, pool, spa/salon, signature ContinuWell initiatives, in virtual/on-demand programs, and in indoor and outdoor spaces across the continuum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designs and implements fitness and wellness programs that address diverse strengths, abilities, interests, and needs. Adapts programs to reflect needs and interests of full continuum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages fitness and spa amenity spaces including fitness equipment space, group exercise studio, pool, salon/spa spaces, indoor and outdoor wellness amenity areas. Maintains amenity spaces in line with Mather standards for presentation, engagement, and safety.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance manages, schedules, and develops Exercise &amp;amp; Wellness Specialists, spa/salon providers, independent contractors. Provides development and training opportunities for exercise &amp;amp; wellness specialists and other colleagues, best practices for adapting wellness programs (including, but not limited to movement, diverse fitness modalities, meditation/breathwork, outdoor experiences, wellness coaching, etc.) across continuum. Follows Mather policies for contractor usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimizes use of fitness &amp;amp; spa budgets across the continuum: provides quality experience and strategically utilize contractors, supplies and services, etc. Drives revenue generation opportunities via personal training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manages creation and utilization of quality on-demand virtual wellness offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
